BEGIN_PGML
In one college math course, the final grade (out of [`100`] points) is calculated by adding one-third of the homework average, one-sixth of the class project score, one-fourth of the midterm score, and one-fourth of the final exam score.

[$p] has [$homework] for [$p->their] homework average, [$project] for [$p->their] class project score, and [$midterm] for [$p->their] midterm score. [$p->Their] goal is to finish the course with a final grade of [$goal]. What must [$p->they] score on the final exam?

[_]{$sol}{16}

END_PGML

